washpool
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a pool in which sheep or wool were washed [usually constructed of a series of dammed pools in a stream and now commemorated in such place names as Washpool, Washpen or Sheepwash Creek.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:sheepwash; woolwash; wash dip
Pronunciation:
